Highest flu rate - one of the cities
The morbidity rate for flu and acute upper respiratory infections (URI) dropped in the whole of the country last week.
According to the Center for Infectious Diseases and AIDS (ULAC), on 29 October - 4 November, the total morbidity rate in Lithuania for flu and acute URI was 49.9 per 10,000 inhabitants.
Last week, this rate was 68.1 per 10,000 inhabitants.
Last year at about the same time, 50.4 cases per 10,000 inhabitants were registered.
The lowest rate - 28.1 cases per 10,000 inhabitants - has been recorded in the Utena administrative territory, whereas the highest rate - 65.5 cases - in the Kaunas administrative territory.
Last week, one child was hospitalized with flu.
