“It's a very rocky, rough terrain and this particular hill has a 120-150 meter rise,” S. Kennedy said.
G.D. Lawrence had been a family’s pilot for many years.
He had also flown helicopters in Vietnam during his service, S. Kennedy said.
An autopsy on the pilot should reveal his physical condition and whether it might have been a factor in the crash.
The helicopter crashed about 5 to 10 minutes after takeoff.
