But the CEC Chairman admitted that if this or next week the Seimas rejected the President’s veto and the new amendments on distribution of the budget money to political parties came into effect, the CEC may consider a decision on assigning an additional grant to individual political forces, including LSDDP.
“Taking our decision, we will take into account the entire legal environment in force, as we are an executive authority that has to implement laws that are adopted,” she said.
